				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: 'splain some stuff to me, please!<a name="40098"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 15 04 5:06 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">1) True or False: There are several different types of play styles for bards - singing bard, tanking bard, buff bard.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
Certainly true, but don't be limited to just one play style. I'm a group/raiding bard, but I started out as a soloer bard. My musical abilities have always been my focus though, with secondary being my physical stats.
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">2) What stats are important to a Bard, based on what type of styles?</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
Stats don't weigh that much really. STA gives more hp, STR gives a little bit of extra attack and lets you carry more, DEX affects your missed notes and melee skill ups, AGI your defensive skill ups. WIS is no use to us, INT affects our manapool, and CHA plays a role in lulling and missed notes. Regardless of race I'd always go for balanced stats, because the focus of which stat you need varies slightly as you grow in levels. And you can always affect that with your gear choices.
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">3) What is &quot;fade&quot;, and why does INT have anything to do with it?</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
&quot;Fade&quot; is an AA ability called Fading Memories, which is available at level 63 and costs 6 AA points. Fade uses 900 mana every time you use it, and since our manapool is based on INT... there you have it. What Fade does is remove you from agro list of all mobs in the zone you might be on, and make you invisible. If the mobs in vicinity see invis, this can fail. 
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">4) How/when does a Bard use mana? (&lt;-----???????) </span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
We use mana roughly for 3 things: Fading Memories, Charm songs (level 39 and 64) and level 43 Dirge. If you charm/swarm kite past level 39 you'll start using mana after the level 27 charm doesn't work anymore. Dirge is very rarely used, it's a targeted AE nuke, kind of a last resort. Fade is what high level bards usually use their mana in.
<br />

<br />
Hope this helps.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
