				<td colspan="2"><span>I think you have a good idea what stats to emphasize now, don't forget to check how much armor class your armor gives, AC does help when you get hit, and you'll get hit quite a few times.
<br />

<br />
There's probably as many playstyles as there are bards, everyone has their own tricks, and there is no single 'right' way to do things. I can do stuff this way and it works, but the bard next to me does the same thing a bit differently, and it works for them! So, if it works for you, don't try to fit in someone else's way of doing things.</span></td>
