				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: 'splain some stuff to me, please!<a name="40226"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 17 04 9:29 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Let me just jump in here.  I am a 40 bard with some recent experience with what the original poster is dealing with.  Basically, I can confirm everything said so far by Lyrisa.
<br />

<br />
I did a lot of tanking in the lower levels when grouped.  I did solo a lot, too.  I find I like grouping over soloing but that's me. Other bards solo most of the time.  It's nice to have choices.  
<br />

<br />
Now, at 40 I find, in groups, I spend most of my time as a ghetto chanter.  I add some extra DPS with melee when I can. Instead of off-tanking I tend to just mezz/charm adds so that I can focus my attention on assisting the main tank (and keep the cleric from getting killed).  Bards make one of the best shields a cleric ever had.
<br />

<br />
When soloing I tend to chant kite. But that gets boring after awhile.  I used to fear kite a lot, too, until I got my 2nd chant.  I never did AoE kiting before but I may try that now that I have a troubador's mace.  </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
